This paper deals with the application of machine learning in the context of fairness and bias, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of semantic relatedness and vector-based similarity, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and data mining, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with legal documents and regulatory policies, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
